Loves programming
When I was young, I thought I "liked programming," but I realized that I "liked to create what I wanted to create by means of programming," and that if I had to divide my time between the task of thinking about what to create and the task of realizing it through programming, which would I choose? If I had to choose between the task of thinking about what to make and the task of realizing it through programming, I would choose the "thinking about what to make" task.

He also "liked to create what he wanted to create by means other than programming (e.g., 3D modeling)" and "liked to make what he wanted to realize happen in natural language.